        <num>CC 757</num>
        <heading>757.  Sufficiency of acts by third persons</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 757.  Sufficiency of acts by third persons.
A predial servitude is preserved by the use made of it by anyone, even a stranger, if it is used as appertaining to the dominant estate.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110952</p>
